<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1894-06-02T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1894-06-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="219" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d219">
                    <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Gresham</persName> to Sir
                                <persName type="to">Julian Pauncefote</persName>.</hi></head>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1894-06-02"><hi rend="italic">June 2,
                            1894</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                    <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Excellency</hi>: I have the honor to inclose herewith
                        for your information copy of a modus vivendi between the United States and
                            Russia<note n="*" xml:id="d219fn1">See <ref target="#pg_158">page
                                158</ref>.</note> for the protection of fur seals in and near the
                        Russian waters of the Bering Sea and in a zone of 30 miles around the
                        Commander and Robben Islands.</p>
                    <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                    <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">W. Q. Gresham.</hi></signed></closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>